channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: DeSantis: One Way or Another, Trump Will Be Able to Vote in Florida
Trump turns conviction into cash, spotlights record fundraising in wake of guilty verdict
item.description: Trump campaign announces haul of $52.8 million in fundraising in the 24 hours after the former president was found guilty on all counts in his criminal trial.

item.title: Matthew Whitaker to Newsmax: We Are on the Precipice of Legal Chaos
item.description: Former Acting Attorney General Matthew Whitaker told Newsmax on Friday that in the wake of the conviction of former President Donald Trump "we are on the precipice of complete and utter chaos in our legal system."

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: The Unique Friendship of Alabama Player Malachi Moore With a Blind Girl Inspires
Kansas Constitution doesn't include right to vote: state high court majority
item.description: The Kansas Supreme Court released a majority opinion Friday suggesting that the state Constitution's Bill of Rights does not include a right to vote.

item.title: Texas AG Paxton to Newsmax: Biden Wants Illegals Voting
item.description: Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton told Newsmax on Friday that the Biden administration has intentionally allowed millions of illegal immigrants to enter the country so Democrats can expand their voter base. "We've seen record numbers of people that have been coming across ...

item.title: Trump Trial Aftermath â€“ GOP Must Implement Legal Reforms Preventing Political Bias
Vermont Gov. Scott vetoes 'safe injection site' proposal
item.description: Republican Vermont Gov. Phil Scott has vetoed the Democratic Legislature's proposal to create a pilot "safe injection site" for drug users in Burlington.

item.title: Classified Doc Case: Prosecutors Renew Bid to Gag Trump
item.description: Prosecutors in former President Donald Trump's classified document case have renewed their request to a federal judge to censor the Republican front-runner after he claimed the FBI was authorized to kill him during a raid on his Mar-a-Lago estate in August 2022.

item.title: Trump Team Nails Biden's Evil Response to Verdict, While He Digs Hole Deeper With New Remarks to Doocy
GOP's Murkowski laments Trump's 'baggage' following guilty verdict
item.description: Sen. Lisa Murkowski, R-Alaska, was one of the last Republicans to comment on former President Trump's conviction, but did not reveal her thoughts on it.

item.title: 15 States Sue to Block HHS' New Gender Identity Rule
item.description: The Republican attorneys general of Mississippi and Tennessee announced Friday that they are part of a multistate lawsuit challenging a new Biden administration rule that redefines Section 1557 of the Affordable Care Act's prohibition against discrimination based on "sex"...

item.title: Joe Biden Has Awkward Mike Dukakis Moment During Trainwreck of a Meeting With the Kansas City Chiefs
Soros heir urges Democrats to hammer Trump as 'convicted felon at every opportunity'
item.description: George Soros' son urged Democrats to wield Trump's conviction against him, constantly referring to him as a "convicted felon," ahead of the election.

item.title: Nikki Haley Silent on Trump Verdict
item.description: As of Friday evening, former Republican Presidential candidate Nikki Haley has yet to weigh in on the conviction of former President Donald Trump by a Manhattan jury of 34 felony charges.
